   35  pub enum AnnNode<'a> {
   36      NodeBlock(&'a ast::Block),

   39      NodePat(&'a ast::Pat),

   42  pub trait PpAnn {
   43      fn pre(&self, _state: &mut State, _node: AnnNode) -> IoResult<()> { Ok(()) }
   44      fn post(&self, _state: &mut State, _node: AnnNode) -> IoResult<()> { Ok(()) }
   45  }

   56  pub struct State<'a> {

   67  pub fn rust_printer(writer: ~io::Writer) -> State<'static> {
   68      static NO_ANN: NoAnn = NoAnn;
   69      rust_printer_annotated(writer, &NO_ANN)
   70  }

   72  pub fn rust_printer_annotated<'a>(writer: ~io::Writer,
   73                                    ann: &'a PpAnn) -> State<'a> {
   74      State {
   75          s: pp::mk_printer(writer, default_columns),
   76          cm: None,
   77          intr: token::get_ident_interner(),
   78          comments: None,
   79          literals: None,
   80          cur_cmnt_and_lit: CurrentCommentAndLiteral {
   81              cur_cmnt: 0,
   82              cur_lit: 0
   83          },
   84          boxes: Vec::new(),
   85          ann: ann
   86      }
   87  }
   88  
   89  pub static indent_unit: uint = 4u;
   90  
   91  pub static default_columns: uint = 78u;
   92  
   93  // Requires you to pass an input filename and reader so that
   94  // it can scan the input text for comments and literals to
   95  // copy forward.
   96  pub fn print_crate<'a>(cm: &'a CodeMap,
   97                         span_diagnostic: &diagnostic::SpanHandler,
   98                         krate: &ast::Crate,
   99                         filename: ~str,
  100                         input: &mut io::Reader,
  101                         out: ~io::Writer,
  102                         ann: &'a PpAnn,
  103                         is_expanded: bool) -> IoResult<()> {
  104      let (cmnts, lits) = comments::gather_comments_and_literals(
  105          span_diagnostic,
  106          filename,
  107          input
  108      );
  109      let mut s = State {
  110          s: pp::mk_printer(out, default_columns),
  111          cm: Some(cm),
  112          intr: token::get_ident_interner(),
  113          comments: Some(cmnts),
  114          // If the code is post expansion, don't use the table of
  115          // literals, since it doesn't correspond with the literals
  116          // in the AST anymore.
  117          literals: if is_expanded {
  118              None
  119          } else {
  120              Some(lits)
  121          },
  122          cur_cmnt_and_lit: CurrentCommentAndLiteral {
  123              cur_cmnt: 0,
  124              cur_lit: 0
  125          },
  126          boxes: Vec::new(),
  127          ann: ann
  128      };
  129      try!(s.print_mod(&krate.module, krate.attrs.as_slice()));
  130      try!(s.print_remaining_comments());
  131      eof(&mut s.s)
  132  }

  134  pub fn to_str(f: |&mut State| -> IoResult<()>) -> ~str {
  135      let mut s = rust_printer(~MemWriter::new());
  136      f(&mut s).unwrap();
  137      eof(&mut s.s).unwrap();
  138      unsafe {
  139          // FIXME(pcwalton): A nasty function to extract the string from an `io::Writer`
  140          // that we "know" to be a `MemWriter` that works around the lack of checked
  141          // downcasts.
  142          let (_, wr): (uint, ~MemWriter) = cast::transmute_copy(&s.s.out);
  143          let result = str::from_utf8_owned(wr.get_ref().to_owned()).unwrap();
  144          cast::forget(wr);
  145          result
  146      }
  147  }

  238  impl<'a> State<'a> {
  239      pub fn ibox(&mut self, u: uint) -> IoResult<()> {
  240          self.boxes.push(pp::Inconsistent);
  241          pp::ibox(&mut self.s, u)
  242      }
  243  
  244      pub fn end(&mut self) -> IoResult<()> {
  245          self.boxes.pop().unwrap();
  246          pp::end(&mut self.s)
  247      }
  248  
  249      pub fn cbox(&mut self, u: uint) -> IoResult<()> {
  250          self.boxes.push(pp::Consistent);
  251          pp::cbox(&mut self.s, u)
  252      }
  253  
  254      // "raw box"
  255      pub fn rbox(&mut self, u: uint, b: pp::Breaks) -> IoResult<()> {
  256          self.boxes.push(b);
  257          pp::rbox(&mut self.s, u, b)
  258      }
  259  
  260      pub fn nbsp(&mut self) -> IoResult<()> { word(&mut self.s, " ") }
  261  
  262      pub fn word_nbsp(&mut self, w: &str) -> IoResult<()> {
  263          try!(word(&mut self.s, w));
  264          self.nbsp()
  265      }
  266  
  267      pub fn word_space(&mut self, w: &str) -> IoResult<()> {
  268          try!(word(&mut self.s, w));
  269          space(&mut self.s)
  270      }
  271  
  272      pub fn popen(&mut self) -> IoResult<()> { word(&mut self.s, "(") }
  273  
  274      pub fn pclose(&mut self) -> IoResult<()> { word(&mut self.s, ")") }
  275  
  276      pub fn head(&mut self, w: &str) -> IoResult<()> {
  277          // outer-box is consistent
  278          try!(self.cbox(indent_unit));
  279          // head-box is inconsistent
  280          try!(self.ibox(w.len() + 1));
  281          // keyword that starts the head
  282          if !w.is_empty() {
  283              try!(self.word_nbsp(w));
  284          }
  285          Ok(())
  286      }
  287  
  288      pub fn bopen(&mut self) -> IoResult<()> {
  289          try!(word(&mut self.s, "{"));
  290          self.end() // close the head-box
  291      }
  292  
  293      pub fn bclose_(&mut self, span: codemap::Span,
  294                     indented: uint) -> IoResult<()> {
  295          self.bclose_maybe_open(span, indented, true)
  296      }
  297      pub fn bclose_maybe_open (&mut self, span: codemap::Span,
  298                                indented: uint, close_box: bool) -> IoResult<()> {
  299          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(span.hi));
  300          try!(self.break_offset_if_not_bol(1u, -(indented as int)));
  301          try!(word(&mut self.s, "}"));
  302          if close_box {
  303              try!(self.end()); // close the outer-box
  304          }
  305          Ok(())
  306      }
  307      pub fn bclose(&mut self, span: codemap::Span) -> IoResult<()> {
  308          self.bclose_(span, indent_unit)
  309      }
  310  
  311      pub fn is_begin(&mut self) -> bool {
  312          match self.s.last_token() { pp::Begin(_) => true, _ => false }
  313      }
  314  
  315      pub fn is_end(&mut self) -> bool {
  316          match self.s.last_token() { pp::End => true, _ => false }
  317      }
  318  
  319      pub fn is_bol(&mut self) -> bool {
  320          self.s.last_token().is_eof() || self.s.last_token().is_hardbreak_tok()
  321      }
  322  
  323      pub fn in_cbox(&self) -> bool {
  324          match self.boxes.last() {
  325              Some(&last_box) => last_box == pp::Consistent,
  326              None => false
  327          }
  328      }
  329  
  330      pub fn hardbreak_if_not_bol(&mut self) -> IoResult<()> {
  331          if !self.is_bol() {
  332              try!(hardbreak(&mut self.s))
  333          }
  334          Ok(())
  335      }
  336      pub fn space_if_not_bol(&mut self) -> IoResult<()> {
  337          if !self.is_bol() { try!(space(&mut self.s)); }
  338          Ok(())
  339      }
  340      pub fn break_offset_if_not_bol(&mut self, n: uint,
  341                                     off: int) -> IoResult<()> {
  342          if !self.is_bol() {
  343              break_offset(&mut self.s, n, off)
  344          } else {
  345              if off != 0 && self.s.last_token().is_hardbreak_tok() {
  346                  // We do something pretty sketchy here: tuck the nonzero
  347                  // offset-adjustment we were going to deposit along with the
  348                  // break into the previous hardbreak.
  349                  self.s.replace_last_token(pp::hardbreak_tok_offset(off));
  350              }
  351              Ok(())
  352          }
  353      }
  354  
  355      // Synthesizes a comment that was not textually present in the original source
  356      // file.
  357      pub fn synth_comment(&mut self, text: ~str) -> IoResult<()> {
  358          try!(word(&mut self.s, "/*"));
  359          try!(space(&mut self.s));
  360          try!(word(&mut self.s, text));
  361          try!(space(&mut self.s));
  362          word(&mut self.s, "*/")
  363      }
  364  
  365      pub fn commasep<T>(&mut self, b: Breaks, elts: &[T],
  366                         op: |&mut State, &T| -> IoResult<()>)
  367          -> IoResult<()> {
  368          try!(self.rbox(0u, b));
  369          let mut first = true;
  370          for elt in elts.iter() {
  371              if first { first = false; } else { try!(self.word_space(",")); }
  372              try!(op(self, elt));
  373          }
  374          self.end()
  375      }
  376  
  377  
  378      pub fn commasep_cmnt<T>(
  379                           &mut self,
  380                           b: Breaks,
  381                           elts: &[T],
  382                           op: |&mut State, &T| -> IoResult<()>,
  383                           get_span: |&T| -> codemap::Span) -> IoResult<()> {
  384          try!(self.rbox(0u, b));
  385          let len = elts.len();
  386          let mut i = 0u;
  387          for elt in elts.iter() {
  388              try!(self.maybe_print_comment(get_span(elt).hi));
  389              try!(op(self, elt));
  390              i += 1u;
  391              if i < len {
  392                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ","));
  393                  try!(self.maybe_print_trailing_comment(get_span(elt),
  394                                                      Some(get_span(&elts[i]).hi)));
  395                  try!(self.space_if_not_bol());
  396              }
  397          }
  398          self.end()
  399      }
  400  
  401      pub fn commasep_exprs(&mut self, b: Breaks,
  402                            exprs: &[@ast::Expr]) -> IoResult<()> {
  403          self.commasep_cmnt(b, exprs, |s, &e| s.print_expr(e), |e| e.span)
  404      }

  438  
  439      pub fn print_type(&mut self, ty: &ast::Ty) -> IoResult<()> {
  440          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(ty.span.lo));
  441          try!(self.ibox(0u));
  442          match ty.node {
  443              ast::TyNil => try!(word(&mut self.s, "()")),
  444              ast::TyBot => try!(word(&mut self.s, "!")),
  445              ast::TyBox(ty) => {
  446                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "@"));
  447                  try!(self.print_type(ty));
  448              }
  449              ast::TyUniq(ty) => {
  450                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "~"));
  451                  try!(self.print_type(ty));
  452              }
  453              ast::TyVec(ty) => {
  454                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "["));
  455                  try!(self.print_type(ty));
  456                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "]"));
  457              }
  458              ast::TyPtr(ref mt) => {
  459                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "*"));
  460                  try!(self.print_mt(mt));
  461              }
  462              ast::TyRptr(ref lifetime, ref mt) => {
  463                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "&"));
  464                  try!(self.print_opt_lifetime(lifetime));
  465                  try!(self.print_mt(mt));
  466              }
  467              ast::TyTup(ref elts) => {
  468                  try!(self.popen());
  469                  try!(self.commasep(Inconsistent, elts.as_slice(),
  470                                     |s, ty| s.print_type_ref(ty)));
  471                  if elts.len() == 1 {
  472                      try!(word(&mut self.s, ","));
  473                  }
  474                  try!(self.pclose());
  475              }
  476              ast::TyBareFn(f) => {
  477                  let generics = ast::Generics {
  478                      lifetimes: f.lifetimes.clone(),
  479                      ty_params: OwnedSlice::empty()
  480                  };
  481                  try!(self.print_ty_fn(Some(f.abi), None, &None,
  482                                     f.purity, ast::Many, f.decl, None, &None,
  483                                     Some(&generics), None));
  484              }
  485              ast::TyClosure(f) => {
  486                  let generics = ast::Generics {
  487                      lifetimes: f.lifetimes.clone(),
  488                      ty_params: OwnedSlice::empty()
  489                  };
  490                  try!(self.print_ty_fn(None, Some(f.sigil), &f.region,
  491                                     f.purity, f.onceness, f.decl, None, &f.bounds,
  492                                     Some(&generics), None));
  493              }
  494              ast::TyPath(ref path, ref bounds, _) => {
  495                  try!(self.print_bounded_path(path, bounds));
  496              }
  497              ast::TyFixedLengthVec(ty, v) => {
  498                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "["));
  499                  try!(self.print_type(ty));
  500                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ", .."));
  501                  try!(self.print_expr(v));
  502                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "]"));
  503              }
  504              ast::TyTypeof(e) => {
  505                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "typeof("));
  506                  try!(self.print_expr(e));
  507                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ")"));
  508              }
  509              ast::TyInfer => {
  510                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "_"));
  511              }
  512          }
  513          self.end()
  514      }
  515  
  516      pub fn print_type_ref(&mut self, ty: &P<ast::Ty>) -> IoResult<()> {
  517          self.print_type(*ty)
  518      }
  519  
  520      pub fn print_foreign_item(&mut self,
  521                                item: &ast::ForeignItem) -> IoResult<()> {
  522          try!(self.hardbreak_if_not_bol());
  523          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(item.span.lo));
  524          try!(self.print_outer_attributes(item.attrs.as_slice()));
  525          match item.node {
  526              ast::ForeignItemFn(decl, ref generics) => {
  527                  try!(self.print_fn(decl, None, abi::Rust, item.ident, generics,
  528                  None, item.vis));
  529                  try!(self.end()); // end head-ibox
  530                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ";"));
  531                  self.end() // end the outer fn box
  532              }
  533              ast::ForeignItemStatic(t, m) => {
  534                  try!(self.head(visibility_qualified(item.vis, "static")));
  535                  if m {
  536                      try!(self.word_space("mut"));
  537                  }
  538                  try!(self.print_ident(item.ident));
  539                  try!(self.word_space(":"));
  540                  try!(self.print_type(t));
  541                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ";"));
  542                  try!(self.end()); // end the head-ibox
  543                  self.end() // end the outer cbox
  544              }
  545          }
  546      }
  547  
  548      pub fn print_item(&mut self, item: &ast::Item) -> IoResult<()> {
  549          try!(self.hardbreak_if_not_bol());
  550          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(item.span.lo));
  551          try!(self.print_outer_attributes(item.attrs.as_slice()));
  552          try!(self.ann.pre(self, NodeItem(item)));
  553          match item.node {
  554              ast::ItemStatic(ty, m, expr) => {
  555                  try!(self.head(visibility_qualified(item.vis, "static")));
  556                  if m == ast::MutMutable {
  557                      try!(self.word_space("mut"));
  558                  }
  559                  try!(self.print_ident(item.ident));
  560                  try!(self.word_space(":"));
  561                  try!(self.print_type(ty));
  562                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
  563                  try!(self.end()); // end the head-ibox
  564  
  565                  try!(self.word_space("="));
  566                  try!(self.print_expr(expr));
  567                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ";"));
  568                  try!(self.end()); // end the outer cbox
  569              }
  570              ast::ItemFn(decl, purity, abi, ref typarams, body) => {
  571                  try!(self.print_fn(
  572                      decl,
  573                      Some(purity),
  574                      abi,
  575                      item.ident,
  576                      typarams,
  577                      None,
  578                      item.vis
  579                  ));
  580                  try!(word(&mut self.s, " "));
  581                  try!(self.print_block_with_attrs(body, item.attrs.as_slice()));
  582              }
  583              ast::ItemMod(ref _mod) => {
  584                  try!(self.head(visibility_qualified(item.vis, "mod")));
  585                  try!(self.print_ident(item.ident));
  586                  try!(self.nbsp());
  587                  try!(self.bopen());
  588                  try!(self.print_mod(_mod, item.attrs.as_slice()));
  589                  try!(self.bclose(item.span));
  590              }
  591              ast::ItemForeignMod(ref nmod) => {
  592                  try!(self.head("extern"));
  593                  try!(self.word_nbsp(nmod.abi.to_str()));
  594                  try!(self.bopen());
  595                  try!(self.print_foreign_mod(nmod, item.attrs.as_slice()));
  596                  try!(self.bclose(item.span));
  597              }
  598              ast::ItemTy(ty, ref params) => {
  599                  try!(self.ibox(indent_unit));
  600                  try!(self.ibox(0u));
  601                  try!(self.word_nbsp(visibility_qualified(item.vis, "type")));
  602                  try!(self.print_ident(item.ident));
  603                  try!(self.print_generics(params));
  604                  try!(self.end()); // end the inner ibox
  605  
  606                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
  607                  try!(self.word_space("="));
  608                  try!(self.print_type(ty));
  609                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ";"));
  610                  try!(self.end()); // end the outer ibox
  611              }
  612              ast::ItemEnum(ref enum_definition, ref params) => {
  613                  try!(self.print_enum_def(
  614                      enum_definition,
  615                      params,
  616                      item.ident,
  617                      item.span,
  618                      item.vis
  619                  ));
  620              }
  621              ast::ItemStruct(struct_def, ref generics) => {
  622                  try!(self.head(visibility_qualified(item.vis, "struct")));
  623                  try!(self.print_struct(struct_def, generics, item.ident, item.span));
  624              }
  625  
  626              ast::ItemImpl(ref generics, ref opt_trait, ty, ref methods) => {
  627                  try!(self.head(visibility_qualified(item.vis, "impl")));
  628                  if generics.is_parameterized() {
  629                      try!(self.print_generics(generics));
  630                      try!(space(&mut self.s));
  631                  }
  632  
  633                  match opt_trait {
  634                      &Some(ref t) => {
  635                          try!(self.print_trait_ref(t));
  636                          try!(space(&mut self.s));
  637                          try!(self.word_space("for"));
  638                      }
  639                      &None => {}
  640                  }
  641  
  642                  try!(self.print_type(ty));
  643  
  644                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
  645                  try!(self.bopen());
  646                  try!(self.print_inner_attributes(item.attrs.as_slice()));
  647                  for meth in methods.iter() {
  648                      try!(self.print_method(*meth));
  649                  }
  650                  try!(self.bclose(item.span));
  651              }
  652              ast::ItemTrait(ref generics, ref traits, ref methods) => {
  653                  try!(self.head(visibility_qualified(item.vis, "trait")));
  654                  try!(self.print_ident(item.ident));
  655                  try!(self.print_generics(generics));
  656                  if traits.len() != 0u {
  657                      try!(word(&mut self.s, ":"));
  658                      for (i, trait_) in traits.iter().enumerate() {
  659                          try!(self.nbsp());
  660                          if i != 0 {
  661                              try!(self.word_space("+"));
  662                          }
  663                          try!(self.print_path(&trait_.path, false));
  664                      }
  665                  }
  666                  try!(word(&mut self.s, " "));
  667                  try!(self.bopen());
  668                  for meth in methods.iter() {
  669                      try!(self.print_trait_method(meth));
  670                  }
  671                  try!(self.bclose(item.span));
  672              }
  673              // I think it's reasonable to hide the context here:
  674              ast::ItemMac(codemap::Spanned { node: ast::MacInvocTT(ref pth, ref tts, _),
  675                                              ..}) => {
  676                  try!(self.print_visibility(item.vis));
  677                  try!(self.print_path(pth, false));
  678                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "! "));
  679                  try!(self.print_ident(item.ident));
  680                  try!(self.cbox(indent_unit));
  681                  try!(self.popen());
  682                  try!(self.print_tts(&(tts.as_slice())));
  683                  try!(self.pclose());
  684                  try!(self.end());
  685              }
  686          }
  687          self.ann.post(self, NodeItem(item))
  688      }
  689  
  690      fn print_trait_ref(&mut self, t: &ast::TraitRef) -> IoResult<()> {
  691          self.print_path(&t.path, false)
  692      }

  694      pub fn print_enum_def(&mut self, enum_definition: &ast::EnumDef,
  695                            generics: &ast::Generics, ident: ast::Ident,
  696                            span: codemap::Span,
  697                            visibility: ast::Visibility) -> IoResult<()> {
  698          try!(self.head(visibility_qualified(visibility, "enum")));
  699          try!(self.print_ident(ident));
  700          try!(self.print_generics(generics));
  701          try!(space(&mut self.s));
  702          self.print_variants(enum_definition.variants.as_slice(), span)
  703      }

  705      pub fn print_variants(&mut self,
  706                            variants: &[P<ast::Variant>],
  707                            span: codemap::Span) -> IoResult<()> {
  708          try!(self.bopen());
  709          for &v in variants.iter() {
  710              try!(self.space_if_not_bol());
  711              try!(self.maybe_print_comment(v.span.lo));
  712              try!(self.print_outer_attributes(v.node.attrs.as_slice()));
  713              try!(self.ibox(indent_unit));
  714              try!(self.print_variant(v));
  715              try!(word(&mut self.s, ","));
  716              try!(self.end());
  717              try!(self.maybe_print_trailing_comment(v.span, None));
  718          }
  719          self.bclose(span)
  720      }

  722      pub fn print_visibility(&mut self, vis: ast::Visibility) -> IoResult<()> {
  723          match vis {
  724              ast::Private => self.word_nbsp("priv"),
  725              ast::Public => self.word_nbsp("pub"),
  726              ast::Inherited => Ok(())
  727          }
  728      }
  729  
  730      pub fn print_struct(&mut self,
  731                          struct_def: &ast::StructDef,
  732                          generics: &ast::Generics,
  733                          ident: ast::Ident,
  734                          span: codemap::Span) -> IoResult<()> {
  735          try!(self.print_ident(ident));
  736          try!(self.print_generics(generics));
  737          if ast_util::struct_def_is_tuple_like(struct_def) {
  738              if !struct_def.fields.is_empty() {
  739                  try!(self.popen());
  740                  try!(self.commasep(
  741                      Inconsistent, struct_def.fields.as_slice(),
  742                      |s, field| {
  743                          match field.node.kind {
  744                              ast::NamedField(..) => fail!("unexpected named field"),
  745                              ast::UnnamedField(vis) => {
  746                                  try!(s.print_visibility(vis));
  747                                  try!(s.maybe_print_comment(field.span.lo));
  748                                  s.print_type(field.node.ty)
  749                              }
  750                          }
  751                      }
  752                  ));
  753                  try!(self.pclose());
  754              }
  755              try!(word(&mut self.s, ";"));
  756              try!(self.end());
  757              self.end() // close the outer-box
  758          } else {
  759              try!(self.nbsp());
  760              try!(self.bopen());
  761              try!(self.hardbreak_if_not_bol());
  762  
  763              for field in struct_def.fields.iter() {
  764                  match field.node.kind {
  765                      ast::UnnamedField(..) => fail!("unexpected unnamed field"),
  766                      ast::NamedField(ident, visibility) => {
  767                          try!(self.hardbreak_if_not_bol());
  768                          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(field.span.lo));
  769                          try!(self.print_outer_attributes(field.node.attrs.as_slice()));
  770                          try!(self.print_visibility(visibility));
  771                          try!(self.print_ident(ident));
  772                          try!(self.word_nbsp(":"));
  773                          try!(self.print_type(field.node.ty));
  774                          try!(word(&mut self.s, ","));
  775                      }
  776                  }
  777              }
  778  
  779              self.bclose(span)
  780          }
  781      }
  782  
  783      /// This doesn't deserve to be called "pretty" printing, but it should be
  784      /// meaning-preserving. A quick hack that might help would be to look at the
  785      /// spans embedded in the TTs to decide where to put spaces and newlines.
  786      /// But it'd be better to parse these according to the grammar of the
  787      /// appropriate macro, transcribe back into the grammar we just parsed from,
  788      /// and then pretty-print the resulting AST nodes (so, e.g., we print
  789      /// expression arguments as expressions). It can be done! I think.
  790      pub fn print_tt(&mut self, tt: &ast::TokenTree) -> IoResult<()> {
  791          match *tt {
  792              ast::TTDelim(ref tts) => self.print_tts(&(tts.as_slice())),
  793              ast::TTTok(_, ref tk) => {
  794                  word(&mut self.s, parse::token::to_str(tk))
  795              }
  796              ast::TTSeq(_, ref tts, ref sep, zerok) => {
  797                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "$("));
  798                  for tt_elt in (*tts).iter() {
  799                      try!(self.print_tt(tt_elt));
  800                  }
  801                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ")"));
  802                  match *sep {
  803                      Some(ref tk) => {
  804                          try!(word(&mut self.s, parse::token::to_str(tk)));
  805                      }
  806                      None => ()
  807                  }
  808                  word(&mut self.s, if zerok { "*" } else { "+" })
  809              }
  810              ast::TTNonterminal(_, name) => {
  811                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "$"));
  812                  self.print_ident(name)
  813              }
  814          }
  815      }
  816  
  817      pub fn print_tts(&mut self, tts: & &[ast::TokenTree]) -> IoResult<()> {
  818          try!(self.ibox(0));
  819          for (i, tt) in tts.iter().enumerate() {
  820              if i != 0 {
  821                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
  822              }
  823              try!(self.print_tt(tt));
  824          }
  825          self.end()
  826      }
  827  
  828      pub fn print_variant(&mut self, v: &ast::Variant) -> IoResult<()> {
  829          try!(self.print_visibility(v.node.vis));
  830          match v.node.kind {
  831              ast::TupleVariantKind(ref args) => {
  832                  try!(self.print_ident(v.node.name));
  833                  if !args.is_empty() {
  834                      try!(self.popen());
  835                      try!(self.commasep(Consistent,
  836                                         args.as_slice(),
  837                                         |s, arg| s.print_type(arg.ty)));
  838                      try!(self.pclose());
  839                  }
  840              }
  841              ast::StructVariantKind(struct_def) => {
  842                  try!(self.head(""));
  843                  let generics = ast_util::empty_generics();
  844                  try!(self.print_struct(struct_def, &generics, v.node.name, v.span));
  845              }
  846          }
  847          match v.node.disr_expr {
  848              Some(d) => {
  849                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
  850                  try!(self.word_space("="));
  851                  self.print_expr(d)
  852              }
  853              _ => Ok(())
  854          }
  855      }
  856  
  857      pub fn print_ty_method(&mut self, m: &ast::TypeMethod) -> IoResult<()> {
  858          try!(self.hardbreak_if_not_bol());
  859          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(m.span.lo));
  860          try!(self.print_outer_attributes(m.attrs.as_slice()));
  861          try!(self.print_ty_fn(None,
  862                                None,
  863                                &None,
  864                                m.purity,
  865                                ast::Many,
  866                                m.decl,
  867                                Some(m.ident),
  868                                &None,
  869                                Some(&m.generics),
  870                                Some(m.explicit_self.node)));
  871          word(&mut self.s, ";")
  872      }

  874      pub fn print_trait_method(&mut self,
  875                                m: &ast::TraitMethod) -> IoResult<()> {
  876          match *m {
  877              Required(ref ty_m) => self.print_ty_method(ty_m),
  878              Provided(m) => self.print_method(m)
  879          }
  880      }

  882      pub fn print_method(&mut self, meth: &ast::Method) -> IoResult<()> {
  883          try!(self.hardbreak_if_not_bol());
  884          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(meth.span.lo));
  885          try!(self.print_outer_attributes(meth.attrs.as_slice()));
  886          try!(self.print_fn(meth.decl, Some(meth.purity), abi::Rust,
  887                          meth.ident, &meth.generics, Some(meth.explicit_self.node),
  888                          meth.vis));
  889          try!(word(&mut self.s, " "));
  890          self.print_block_with_attrs(meth.body, meth.attrs.as_slice())
  891      }

  893      pub fn print_outer_attributes(&mut self,
  894                                    attrs: &[ast::Attribute]) -> IoResult<()> {
  895          let mut count = 0;
  896          for attr in attrs.iter() {
  897              match attr.node.style {
  898                  ast::AttrOuter => {
  899                      try!(self.print_attribute(attr));
  900                      count += 1;
  901                  }
  902                  _ => {/* fallthrough */ }
  903              }
  904          }
  905          if count > 0 {
  906              try!(self.hardbreak_if_not_bol());
  907          }
  908          Ok(())
  909      }

  911      pub fn print_inner_attributes(&mut self,
  912                                    attrs: &[ast::Attribute]) -> IoResult<()> {
  913          let mut count = 0;
  914          for attr in attrs.iter() {
  915              match attr.node.style {
  916                  ast::AttrInner => {
  917                      try!(self.print_attribute(attr));
  918                      count += 1;
  919                  }
  920                  _ => {/* fallthrough */ }
  921              }
  922          }
  923          if count > 0 {
  924              try!(self.hardbreak_if_not_bol());
  925          }
  926          Ok(())
  927      }

  929      pub fn print_attribute(&mut self, attr: &ast::Attribute) -> IoResult<()> {
  930          try!(self.hardbreak_if_not_bol());
  931          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(attr.span.lo));
  932          if attr.node.is_sugared_doc {
  933              word(&mut self.s, attr.value_str().unwrap().get())
  934          } else {
  935              match attr.node.style {
  936                  ast::AttrInner => try!(word(&mut self.s, "#![")),
  937                  ast::AttrOuter => try!(word(&mut self.s, "#[")),
  938              }
  939              try!(self.print_meta_item(attr.meta()));
  940              word(&mut self.s, "]")
  941          }
  942      }

  945      pub fn print_stmt(&mut self, st: &ast::Stmt) -> IoResult<()> {
  946          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(st.span.lo));
  947          match st.node {
  948              ast::StmtDecl(decl, _) => {
  949                  try!(self.print_decl(decl));
  950              }
  951              ast::StmtExpr(expr, _) => {
  952                  try!(self.space_if_not_bol());
  953                  try!(self.print_expr(expr));
  954              }
  955              ast::StmtSemi(expr, _) => {
  956                  try!(self.space_if_not_bol());
  957                  try!(self.print_expr(expr));
  958                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ";"));
  959              }
  960              ast::StmtMac(ref mac, semi) => {
  961                  try!(self.space_if_not_bol());
  962                  try!(self.print_mac(mac));
  963                  if semi {
  964                      try!(word(&mut self.s, ";"));
  965                  }
  966              }
  967          }
  968          if parse::classify::stmt_ends_with_semi(st) {
  969              try!(word(&mut self.s, ";"));
  970          }
  971          self.maybe_print_trailing_comment(st.span, None)
  972      }

  982      pub fn print_block_unclosed_indent(&mut self, blk: &ast::Block,
  983                                         indented: uint) -> IoResult<()> {

  987      pub fn print_block_with_attrs(&mut self,
  988                                    blk: &ast::Block,
  989                                    attrs: &[ast::Attribute]) -> IoResult<()> {
  990          self.print_block_maybe_unclosed(blk, indent_unit, attrs, true)
  991      }
  992  
  993      pub fn print_block_maybe_unclosed(&mut self,
  994                                        blk: &ast::Block,
  995                                        indented: uint,
  996                                        attrs: &[ast::Attribute],
  997                                        close_box: bool) -> IoResult<()> {
  998          match blk.rules {
  999              ast::UnsafeBlock(..) => try!(self.word_space("unsafe")),
 1000              ast::DefaultBlock => ()
 1001          }
 1002          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(blk.span.lo));
 1003          try!(self.ann.pre(self, NodeBlock(blk)));
 1004          try!(self.bopen());
 1005  
 1006          try!(self.print_inner_attributes(attrs));
 1007  
 1008          for vi in blk.view_items.iter() {
 1009              try!(self.print_view_item(vi));
 1010          }
 1011          for st in blk.stmts.iter() {
 1012              try!(self.print_stmt(*st));
 1013          }
 1014          match blk.expr {
 1015              Some(expr) => {
 1016                  try!(self.space_if_not_bol());
 1017                  try!(self.print_expr(expr));
 1018                  try!(self.maybe_print_trailing_comment(expr.span, Some(blk.span.hi)));
 1019              }
 1020              _ => ()
 1021          }
 1022          try!(self.bclose_maybe_open(blk.span, indented, close_box));
 1023          self.ann.post(self, NodeBlock(blk))
 1024      }
 1025  
 1026      fn print_else(&mut self, els: Option<@ast::Expr>) -> IoResult<()> {
 1027          match els {
 1028              Some(_else) => {
 1029                  match _else.node {
 1030                      // "another else-if"
 1031                      ast::ExprIf(i, t, e) => {
 1032                          try!(self.cbox(indent_unit - 1u));
 1033                          try!(self.ibox(0u));
 1034                          try!(word(&mut self.s, " else if "));
 1035                          try!(self.print_expr(i));
 1036                          try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1037                          try!(self.print_block(t));
 1038                          self.print_else(e)
 1039                      }
 1040                      // "final else"
 1041                      ast::ExprBlock(b) => {
 1042                          try!(self.cbox(indent_unit - 1u));
 1043                          try!(self.ibox(0u));
 1044                          try!(word(&mut self.s, " else "));
 1045                          self.print_block(b)
 1046                      }
 1047                      // BLEAH, constraints would be great here
 1048                      _ => {
 1049                          fail!("print_if saw if with weird alternative");
 1050                      }
 1051                  }
 1052              }
 1053              _ => Ok(())
 1054          }
 1055      }
 1056  
 1057      pub fn print_if(&mut self, test: &ast::Expr, blk: &ast::Block,
 1058                      elseopt: Option<@ast::Expr>, chk: bool) -> IoResult<()> {
 1059          try!(self.head("if"));
 1060          if chk { try!(self.word_nbsp("check")); }
 1061          try!(self.print_expr(test));
 1062          try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1063          try!(self.print_block(blk));
 1064          self.print_else(elseopt)
 1065      }

 1097      pub fn print_expr(&mut self, expr: &ast::Expr) -> IoResult<()> {
 1098          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(expr.span.lo));
 1099          try!(self.ibox(indent_unit));
 1100          try!(self.ann.pre(self, NodeExpr(expr)));
 1101          match expr.node {
 1102              ast::ExprVstore(e, v) => {
 1103                  try!(self.print_expr_vstore(v));
 1104                  try!(self.print_expr(e));
 1105              },
 1106              ast::ExprBox(p, e) => {
 1107                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "box"));
 1108                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "("));
 1109                  try!(self.print_expr(p));
 1110                  try!(self.word_space(")"));
 1111                  try!(self.print_expr(e));
 1112              }
 1113              ast::ExprVec(ref exprs) => {
 1114                  try!(self.ibox(indent_unit));
 1115                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "["));
 1116                  try!(self.commasep_exprs(Inconsistent, exprs.as_slice()));
 1117                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "]"));
 1118                  try!(self.end());
 1119              }
 1120  
 1121              ast::ExprRepeat(element, count) => {
 1122                  try!(self.ibox(indent_unit));
 1123                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "["));
 1124                  try!(self.print_expr(element));
 1125                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ","));
 1126                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ".."));
 1127                  try!(self.print_expr(count));
 1128                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "]"));
 1129                  try!(self.end());
 1130              }
 1131  
 1132              ast::ExprStruct(ref path, ref fields, wth) => {
 1133                  try!(self.print_path(path, true));
 1134                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "{"));
 1135                  try!(self.commasep_cmnt(
 1136                      Consistent,
 1137                      fields.as_slice(),
 1138                      |s, field| {
 1139                          try!(s.ibox(indent_unit));
 1140                          try!(s.print_ident(field.ident.node));
 1141                          try!(s.word_space(":"));
 1142                          try!(s.print_expr(field.expr));
 1143                          s.end()
 1144                      },
 1145                      |f| f.span));
 1146                  match wth {
 1147                      Some(expr) => {
 1148                          try!(self.ibox(indent_unit));
 1149                          if !fields.is_empty() {
 1150                              try!(word(&mut self.s, ","));
 1151                              try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1152                          }
 1153                          try!(word(&mut self.s, ".."));
 1154                          try!(self.print_expr(expr));
 1155                          try!(self.end());
 1156                      }
 1157                      _ => try!(word(&mut self.s, ","))
 1158                  }
 1159                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "}"));
 1160              }
 1161              ast::ExprTup(ref exprs) => {
 1162                  try!(self.popen());
 1163                  try!(self.commasep_exprs(Inconsistent, exprs.as_slice()));
 1164                  if exprs.len() == 1 {
 1165                      try!(word(&mut self.s, ","));
 1166                  }
 1167                  try!(self.pclose());
 1168              }
 1169              ast::ExprCall(func, ref args) => {
 1170                  try!(self.print_expr(func));
 1171                  try!(self.print_call_post(args.as_slice()));
 1172              }
 1173              ast::ExprMethodCall(ident, ref tys, ref args) => {
 1174                  let base_args = args.slice_from(1);
 1175                  try!(self.print_expr(*args.get(0)));
 1176                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "."));
 1177                  try!(self.print_ident(ident));
 1178                  if tys.len() > 0u {
 1179                      try!(word(&mut self.s, "::<"));
 1180                      try!(self.commasep(Inconsistent, tys.as_slice(),
 1181                                         |s, ty| s.print_type_ref(ty)));
 1182                      try!(word(&mut self.s, ">"));
 1183                  }
 1184                  try!(self.print_call_post(base_args));
 1185              }
 1186              ast::ExprBinary(op, lhs, rhs) => {
 1187                  try!(self.print_expr(lhs));
 1188                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1189                  try!(self.word_space(ast_util::binop_to_str(op)));
 1190                  try!(self.print_expr(rhs));
 1191              }
 1192              ast::ExprUnary(op, expr) => {
 1193                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ast_util::unop_to_str(op)));
 1194                  try!(self.print_expr(expr));
 1195              }
 1196              ast::ExprAddrOf(m, expr) => {
 1197                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "&"));
 1198                  try!(self.print_mutability(m));
 1199                  // Avoid `& &e` => `&&e`.
 1200                  match (m, &expr.node) {
 1201                      (ast::MutImmutable, &ast::ExprAddrOf(..)) => try!(space(&mut self.s)),
 1202                      _ => { }
 1203                  }
 1204                  try!(self.print_expr(expr));
 1205              }
 1206              ast::ExprLit(lit) => try!(self.print_literal(lit)),
 1207              ast::ExprCast(expr, ty) => {
 1208                  try!(self.print_expr(expr));
 1209                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1210                  try!(self.word_space("as"));
 1211                  try!(self.print_type(ty));
 1212              }
 1213              ast::ExprIf(test, blk, elseopt) => {
 1214                  try!(self.print_if(test, blk, elseopt, false));
 1215              }
 1216              ast::ExprWhile(test, blk) => {
 1217                  try!(self.head("while"));
 1218                  try!(self.print_expr(test));
 1219                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1220                  try!(self.print_block(blk));
 1221              }
 1222              ast::ExprForLoop(pat, iter, blk, opt_ident) => {
 1223                  for ident in opt_ident.iter() {
 1224                      try!(word(&mut self.s, "'"));
 1225                      try!(self.print_ident(*ident));
 1226                      try!(self.word_space(":"));
 1227                  }
 1228                  try!(self.head("for"));
 1229                  try!(self.print_pat(pat));
 1230                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1231                  try!(self.word_space("in"));
 1232                  try!(self.print_expr(iter));
 1233                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1234                  try!(self.print_block(blk));
 1235              }
 1236              ast::ExprLoop(blk, opt_ident) => {
 1237                  for ident in opt_ident.iter() {
 1238                      try!(word(&mut self.s, "'"));
 1239                      try!(self.print_ident(*ident));
 1240                      try!(self.word_space(":"));
 1241                  }
 1242                  try!(self.head("loop"));
 1243                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1244                  try!(self.print_block(blk));
 1245              }
 1246              ast::ExprMatch(expr, ref arms) => {
 1247                  try!(self.cbox(indent_unit));
 1248                  try!(self.ibox(4));
 1249                  try!(self.word_nbsp("match"));
 1250                  try!(self.print_expr(expr));
 1251                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1252                  try!(self.bopen());
 1253                  let len = arms.len();
 1254                  for (i, arm) in arms.iter().enumerate() {
 1255                      try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1256                      try!(self.cbox(indent_unit));
 1257                      try!(self.ibox(0u));
 1258                      let mut first = true;
 1259                      for p in arm.pats.iter() {
 1260                          if first {
 1261                              first = false;
 1262                          } else {
 1263                              try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1264                              try!(self.word_space("|"));
 1265                          }
 1266                          try!(self.print_pat(*p));
 1267                      }
 1268                      try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1269                      match arm.guard {
 1270                          Some(e) => {
 1271                              try!(self.word_space("if"));
 1272                              try!(self.print_expr(e));
 1273                              try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1274                          }
 1275                          None => ()
 1276                      }
 1277                      try!(self.word_space("=>"));
 1278  
 1279                      match arm.body.node {
 1280                          ast::ExprBlock(blk) => {
 1281                              // the block will close the pattern's ibox
 1282                              try!(self.print_block_unclosed_indent(blk, indent_unit));
 1283                          }
 1284                          _ => {
 1285                              try!(self.end()); // close the ibox for the pattern
 1286                              try!(self.print_expr(arm.body));
 1287                          }
 1288                      }
 1289                      if !expr_is_simple_block(expr)
 1290                          && i < len - 1 {
 1291                          try!(word(&mut self.s, ","));
 1292                      }
 1293                      try!(self.end()); // close enclosing cbox
 1294                  }
 1295                  try!(self.bclose_(expr.span, indent_unit));
 1296              }
 1297              ast::ExprFnBlock(decl, body) => {
 1298                  // in do/for blocks we don't want to show an empty
 1299                  // argument list, but at this point we don't know which
 1300                  // we are inside.
 1301                  //
 1302                  // if !decl.inputs.is_empty() {
 1303                  try!(self.print_fn_block_args(decl));
 1304                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1305                  // }
 1306                  assert!(body.stmts.is_empty());
 1307                  assert!(body.expr.is_some());
 1308                  // we extract the block, so as not to create another set of boxes
 1309                  match body.expr.unwrap().node {
 1310                      ast::ExprBlock(blk) => {
 1311                          try!(self.print_block_unclosed(blk));
 1312                      }
 1313                      _ => {
 1314                          // this is a bare expression
 1315                          try!(self.print_expr(body.expr.unwrap()));
 1316                          try!(self.end()); // need to close a box
 1317                      }
 1318                  }
 1319                  // a box will be closed by print_expr, but we didn't want an overall
 1320                  // wrapper so we closed the corresponding opening. so create an
 1321                  // empty box to satisfy the close.
 1322                  try!(self.ibox(0));
 1323              }
 1324              ast::ExprProc(decl, body) => {
 1325                  // in do/for blocks we don't want to show an empty
 1326                  // argument list, but at this point we don't know which
 1327                  // we are inside.
 1328                  //
 1329                  // if !decl.inputs.is_empty() {
 1330                  try!(self.print_proc_args(decl));
 1331                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1332                  // }
 1333                  assert!(body.stmts.is_empty());
 1334                  assert!(body.expr.is_some());
 1335                  // we extract the block, so as not to create another set of boxes
 1336                  match body.expr.unwrap().node {
 1337                      ast::ExprBlock(blk) => {
 1338                          try!(self.print_block_unclosed(blk));
 1339                      }
 1340                      _ => {
 1341                          // this is a bare expression
 1342                          try!(self.print_expr(body.expr.unwrap()));
 1343                          try!(self.end()); // need to close a box
 1344                      }
 1345                  }
 1346                  // a box will be closed by print_expr, but we didn't want an overall
 1347                  // wrapper so we closed the corresponding opening. so create an
 1348                  // empty box to satisfy the close.
 1349                  try!(self.ibox(0));
 1350              }
 1351              ast::ExprBlock(blk) => {
 1352                  // containing cbox, will be closed by print-block at }
 1353                  try!(self.cbox(indent_unit));
 1354                  // head-box, will be closed by print-block after {
 1355                  try!(self.ibox(0u));
 1356                  try!(self.print_block(blk));
 1357              }
 1358              ast::ExprAssign(lhs, rhs) => {
 1359                  try!(self.print_expr(lhs));
 1360                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1361                  try!(self.word_space("="));
 1362                  try!(self.print_expr(rhs));
 1363              }
 1364              ast::ExprAssignOp(op, lhs, rhs) => {
 1365                  try!(self.print_expr(lhs));
 1366                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1367                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ast_util::binop_to_str(op)));
 1368                  try!(self.word_space("="));
 1369                  try!(self.print_expr(rhs));
 1370              }
 1371              ast::ExprField(expr, id, ref tys) => {
 1372                  try!(self.print_expr(expr));
 1373                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "."));
 1374                  try!(self.print_ident(id));
 1375                  if tys.len() > 0u {
 1376                      try!(word(&mut self.s, "::<"));
 1377                      try!(self.commasep(
 1378                          Inconsistent, tys.as_slice(),
 1379                          |s, ty| s.print_type_ref(ty)));
 1380                      try!(word(&mut self.s, ">"));
 1381                  }
 1382              }
 1383              ast::ExprIndex(expr, index) => {
 1384                  try!(self.print_expr(expr));
 1385                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "["));
 1386                  try!(self.print_expr(index));
 1387                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "]"));
 1388              }
 1389              ast::ExprPath(ref path) => try!(self.print_path(path, true)),
 1390              ast::ExprBreak(opt_ident) => {
 1391                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "break"));
 1392                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1393                  for ident in opt_ident.iter() {
 1394                      try!(word(&mut self.s, "'"));
 1395                      try!(self.print_ident(*ident));
 1396                      try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1397                  }
 1398              }
 1399              ast::ExprAgain(opt_ident) => {
 1400                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "continue"));
 1401                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1402                  for ident in opt_ident.iter() {
 1403                      try!(word(&mut self.s, "'"));
 1404                      try!(self.print_ident(*ident));
 1405                      try!(space(&mut self.s))
 1406                  }
 1407              }
 1408              ast::ExprRet(result) => {
 1409                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "return"));
 1410                  match result {
 1411                      Some(expr) => {
 1412                          try!(word(&mut self.s, " "));
 1413                          try!(self.print_expr(expr));
 1414                      }
 1415                      _ => ()
 1416                  }
 1417              }
 1418              ast::ExprInlineAsm(ref a) => {
 1419                  if a.volatile {
 1420                      try!(word(&mut self.s, "__volatile__ asm!"));
 1421                  } else {
 1422                      try!(word(&mut self.s, "asm!"));
 1423                  }
 1424                  try!(self.popen());
 1425                  try!(self.print_string(a.asm.get(), a.asm_str_style));
 1426                  try!(self.word_space(":"));
 1427                  for &(ref co, o) in a.outputs.iter() {
 1428                      try!(self.print_string(co.get(), ast::CookedStr));
 1429                      try!(self.popen());
 1430                      try!(self.print_expr(o));
 1431                      try!(self.pclose());
 1432                      try!(self.word_space(","));
 1433                  }
 1434                  try!(self.word_space(":"));
 1435                  for &(ref co, o) in a.inputs.iter() {
 1436                      try!(self.print_string(co.get(), ast::CookedStr));
 1437                      try!(self.popen());
 1438                      try!(self.print_expr(o));
 1439                      try!(self.pclose());
 1440                      try!(self.word_space(","));
 1441                  }
 1442                  try!(self.word_space(":"));
 1443                  try!(self.print_string(a.clobbers.get(), ast::CookedStr));
 1444                  try!(self.pclose());
 1445              }
 1446              ast::ExprMac(ref m) => try!(self.print_mac(m)),
 1447              ast::ExprParen(e) => {
 1448                  try!(self.popen());
 1449                  try!(self.print_expr(e));
 1450                  try!(self.pclose());
 1451              }
 1452          }
 1453          try!(self.ann.post(self, NodeExpr(expr)));
 1454          self.end()
 1455      }

 1509      fn print_path_(&mut self,
 1510                     path: &ast::Path,
 1511                     colons_before_params: bool,
 1512                     opt_bounds: &Option<OwnedSlice<ast::TyParamBound>>)
 1513          -> IoResult<()> {
 1514          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(path.span.lo));
 1515          if path.global {
 1516              try!(word(&mut self.s, "::"));
 1517          }
 1518  
 1519          let mut first = true;
 1520          for segment in path.segments.iter() {
 1521              if first {
 1522                  first = false
 1523              } else {
 1524                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "::"))
 1525              }
 1526  
 1527              try!(self.print_ident(segment.identifier));
 1528  
 1529              if !segment.lifetimes.is_empty() || !segment.types.is_empty() {
 1530                  if colons_before_params {
 1531                      try!(word(&mut self.s, "::"))
 1532                  }
 1533                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "<"));
 1534  
 1535                  let mut comma = false;
 1536                  for lifetime in segment.lifetimes.iter() {
 1537                      if comma {
 1538                          try!(self.word_space(","))
 1539                      }
 1540                      try!(self.print_lifetime(lifetime));
 1541                      comma = true;
 1542                  }
 1543  
 1544                  if !segment.types.is_empty() {
 1545                      if comma {
 1546                          try!(self.word_space(","))
 1547                      }
 1548                      try!(self.commasep(
 1549                          Inconsistent,
 1550                          segment.types.as_slice(),
 1551                          |s, ty| s.print_type_ref(ty)));
 1552                  }
 1553  
 1554                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ">"))
 1555              }
 1556          }
 1557  
 1558          match *opt_bounds {
 1559              None => Ok(()),
 1560              Some(ref bounds) => self.print_bounds(&None, bounds, true),
 1561          }
 1562      }

 1564      fn print_path(&mut self, path: &ast::Path,

 1567      }

 1575      pub fn print_pat(&mut self, pat: &ast::Pat) -> IoResult<()> {
 1576          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(pat.span.lo));
 1577          try!(self.ann.pre(self, NodePat(pat)));
 1578          /* Pat isn't normalized, but the beauty of it
 1579           is that it doesn't matter */
 1580          match pat.node {
 1581              ast::PatWild => try!(word(&mut self.s, "_")),
 1582              ast::PatWildMulti => try!(word(&mut self.s, "..")),
 1583              ast::PatIdent(binding_mode, ref path, sub) => {
 1584                  match binding_mode {
 1585                      ast::BindByRef(mutbl) => {
 1586                          try!(self.word_nbsp("ref"));
 1587                          try!(self.print_mutability(mutbl));
 1588                      }
 1589                      ast::BindByValue(ast::MutImmutable) => {}
 1590                      ast::BindByValue(ast::MutMutable) => {
 1591                          try!(self.word_nbsp("mut"));
 1592                      }
 1593                  }
 1594                  try!(self.print_path(path, true));
 1595                  match sub {
 1596                      Some(p) => {
 1597                          try!(word(&mut self.s, "@"));
 1598                          try!(self.print_pat(p));
 1599                      }
 1600                      None => ()
 1601                  }
 1602              }
 1603              ast::PatEnum(ref path, ref args_) => {
 1604                  try!(self.print_path(path, true));
 1605                  match *args_ {
 1606                      None => try!(word(&mut self.s, "(..)")),
 1607                      Some(ref args) => {
 1608                          if !args.is_empty() {
 1609                              try!(self.popen());
 1610                              try!(self.commasep(Inconsistent, args.as_slice(),
 1611                                                |s, &p| s.print_pat(p)));
 1612                              try!(self.pclose());
 1613                          }
 1614                      }
 1615                  }
 1616              }
 1617              ast::PatStruct(ref path, ref fields, etc) => {
 1618                  try!(self.print_path(path, true));
 1619                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "{"));
 1620                  try!(self.commasep_cmnt(
 1621                      Consistent, fields.as_slice(),
 1622                      |s, f| {
 1623                          try!(s.cbox(indent_unit));
 1624                          try!(s.print_ident(f.ident));
 1625                          try!(s.word_space(":"));
 1626                          try!(s.print_pat(f.pat));
 1627                          s.end()
 1628                      },
 1629                      |f| f.pat.span));
 1630                  if etc {
 1631                      if fields.len() != 0u { try!(self.word_space(",")); }
 1632                      try!(word(&mut self.s, ".."));
 1633                  }
 1634                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "}"));
 1635              }
 1636              ast::PatTup(ref elts) => {
 1637                  try!(self.popen());
 1638                  try!(self.commasep(Inconsistent,
 1639                                     elts.as_slice(),
 1640                                     |s, &p| s.print_pat(p)));
 1641                  if elts.len() == 1 {
 1642                      try!(word(&mut self.s, ","));
 1643                  }
 1644                  try!(self.pclose());
 1645              }
 1646              ast::PatUniq(inner) => {
 1647                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "~"));
 1648                  try!(self.print_pat(inner));
 1649              }
 1650              ast::PatRegion(inner) => {
 1651                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "&"));
 1652                  try!(self.print_pat(inner));
 1653              }
 1654              ast::PatLit(e) => try!(self.print_expr(e)),
 1655              ast::PatRange(begin, end) => {
 1656                  try!(self.print_expr(begin));
 1657                  try!(space(&mut self.s));
 1658                  try!(word(&mut self.s, ".."));
 1659                  try!(self.print_expr(end));
 1660              }
 1661              ast::PatVec(ref before, slice, ref after) => {
 1662                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "["));
 1663                  try!(self.commasep(Inconsistent,
 1664                                     before.as_slice(),
 1665                                     |s, &p| s.print_pat(p)));
 1666                  for &p in slice.iter() {
 1667                      if !before.is_empty() { try!(self.word_space(",")); }
 1668                      match *p {
 1669                          ast::Pat { node: ast::PatWildMulti, .. } => {
 1670                              // this case is handled by print_pat
 1671                          }
 1672                          _ => try!(word(&mut self.s, "..")),
 1673                      }
 1674                      try!(self.print_pat(p));
 1675                      if !after.is_empty() { try!(self.word_space(",")); }
 1676                  }
 1677                  try!(self.commasep(Inconsistent,
 1678                                     after.as_slice(),
 1679                                     |s, &p| s.print_pat(p)));
 1680                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "]"));
 1681              }
 1682          }
 1683          self.ann.post(self, NodePat(pat))
 1684      }

 1726      pub fn print_fn_args(&mut self, decl: &ast::FnDecl,
 1727                           opt_explicit_self: Option<ast::ExplicitSelf_>)
 1728          -> IoResult<()> {
 1729          // It is unfortunate to duplicate the commasep logic, but we want the
 1730          // self type and the args all in the same box.
 1731          try!(self.rbox(0u, Inconsistent));
 1732          let mut first = true;
 1733          for &explicit_self in opt_explicit_self.iter() {
 1734              let m = match explicit_self {
 1735                  ast::SelfStatic => ast::MutImmutable,
 1736                  _ => match decl.inputs.get(0).pat.node {
 1737                      ast::PatIdent(ast::BindByValue(m), _, _) => m,
 1738                      _ => ast::MutImmutable
 1739                  }
 1740              };
 1741              first = !try!(self.print_explicit_self(explicit_self, m));
 1742          }
 1743  
 1744          // HACK(eddyb) ignore the separately printed self argument.
 1745          let args = if first {

 1816      pub fn print_bounds(&mut self,
 1817                          region: &Option<ast::Lifetime>,
 1818                          bounds: &OwnedSlice<ast::TyParamBound>,
 1819                          print_colon_anyway: bool) -> IoResult<()> {
 1820          if !bounds.is_empty() || region.is_some() {
 1821              try!(word(&mut self.s, ":"));
 1822              let mut first = true;
 1823              match *region {
 1824                  Some(ref lt) => {
 1825                      let token = token::get_name(lt.name);
 1826                      if token.get() != "static" {
 1827                          try!(self.nbsp());
 1828                          first = false;
 1829                          try!(self.print_lifetime(lt));
 1830                      }
 1831                  }
 1832                  None => {}
 1833              }
 1834              for bound in bounds.iter() {
 1835                  try!(self.nbsp());
 1836                  if first {
 1837                      first = false;
 1838                  } else {
 1839                      try!(self.word_space("+"));
 1840                  }
 1841  
 1842                  try!(match *bound {
 1843                      TraitTyParamBound(ref tref) => self.print_trait_ref(tref),
 1844                      RegionTyParamBound => word(&mut self.s, "'static"),
 1845                  })
 1846              }
 1847              Ok(())
 1848          } else if print_colon_anyway {
 1849              word(&mut self.s, ":")
 1850          } else {
 1851              Ok(())
 1852          }
 1853      }

 1861      pub fn print_generics(&mut self,
 1862                            generics: &ast::Generics) -> IoResult<()> {
 1863          let total = generics.lifetimes.len() + generics.ty_params.len();
 1864          if total > 0 {
 1865              try!(word(&mut self.s, "<"));
 1866  
 1867              let mut ints = Vec::new();
 1868              for i in range(0u, total) {
 1869                  ints.push(i);
 1870              }
 1871  
 1872              try!(self.commasep(
 1873                  Inconsistent, ints.as_slice(),
 1874                  |s, &idx| {
 1875                      if idx < generics.lifetimes.len() {
 1876                          let lifetime = generics.lifetimes.get(idx);
 1877                          s.print_lifetime(lifetime)
 1878                      } else {
 1879                          let idx = idx - generics.lifetimes.len();
 1880                          let param = generics.ty_params.get(idx);
 1881                          try!(s.print_ident(param.ident));
 1882                          try!(s.print_bounds(&None, &param.bounds, false));
 1883                          match param.default {
 1884                              Some(default) => {
 1885                                  try!(space(&mut s.s));
 1886                                  try!(s.word_space("="));
 1887                                  s.print_type(default)
 1888                              }
 1889                              _ => Ok(())
 1890                          }
 1891                      }
 1892                  }));
 1893              word(&mut self.s, ">")
 1894          } else {
 1895              Ok(())
 1896          }
 1897      }

 2023      pub fn print_ty_fn(&mut self,

 2105      pub fn maybe_print_trailing_comment(&mut self, span: codemap::Span,
 2106                                          next_pos: Option<BytePos>)
 2107          -> IoResult<()> {
 2108          let cm = match self.cm {
 2109              Some(cm) => cm,
 2110              _ => return Ok(())
 2111          };
 2112          match self.next_comment() {
 2113              Some(ref cmnt) => {
 2114                  if (*cmnt).style != comments::Trailing { return Ok(()) }
 2115                  let span_line = cm.lookup_char_pos(span.hi);
 2116                  let comment_line = cm.lookup_char_pos((*cmnt).pos);
 2117                  let mut next = (*cmnt).pos + BytePos(1);
 2118                  match next_pos { None => (), Some(p) => next = p }
 2119                  if span.hi < (*cmnt).pos && (*cmnt).pos < next &&
 2120                      span_line.line == comment_line.line {
 2121                          try!(self.print_comment(cmnt));
 2122                          self.cur_cmnt_and_lit.cur_cmnt += 1u;
 2123                      }
 2124              }
 2125              _ => ()
 2126          }
 2127          Ok(())
 2128      }

 2148      pub fn print_literal(&mut self, lit: &ast::Lit) -> IoResult<()> {
 2149          try!(self.maybe_print_comment(lit.span.lo));
 2150          match self.next_lit(lit.span.lo) {
 2151              Some(ref ltrl) => {
 2152                  return word(&mut self.s, (*ltrl).lit);
 2153              }
 2154              _ => ()
 2155          }
 2156          match lit.node {
 2157              ast::LitStr(ref st, style) => self.print_string(st.get(), style),
 2158              ast::LitChar(ch) => {
 2159                  let mut res = ~"'";
 2160                  char::from_u32(ch).unwrap().escape_default(|c| res.push_char(c));

 2163              }
 2164              ast::LitInt(i, t) => {
 2165                  word(&mut self.s, format!("{}{}", i, ast_util::int_ty_to_str(t)))
 2166              }
 2167              ast::LitUint(u, t) => {
 2168                  word(&mut self.s, format!("{}{}", u, ast_util::uint_ty_to_str(t)))
 2169              }
 2170              ast::LitIntUnsuffixed(i) => {

 2173              ast::LitFloat(ref f, t) => {
 2174                  word(&mut self.s, f.get() + ast_util::float_ty_to_str(t))
 2175              }
 2176              ast::LitFloatUnsuffixed(ref f) => word(&mut self.s, f.get()),
 2177              ast::LitNil => word(&mut self.s, "()"),
 2178              ast::LitBool(val) => {
 2179                  if val { word(&mut self.s, "true") } else { word(&mut self.s, "false") }
 2180              }
 2181              ast::LitBinary(ref arr) => {
 2182                  try!(self.ibox(indent_unit));
 2183                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "["));
 2184                  try!(self.commasep_cmnt(Inconsistent, arr.as_slice(),
 2185                                          |s, u| word(&mut s.s, format!("{}", *u)),
 2186                                          |_| lit.span));
 2187                  try!(word(&mut self.s, "]"));
 2188                  self.end()
 2189              }
 2190          }
 2191      }

 2193      pub fn next_lit(&mut self, pos: BytePos) -> Option<comments::Literal> {
 2194          match self.literals {
 2195              Some(ref lits) => {

 2223      pub fn print_comment(&mut self,
 2224                           cmnt: &comments::Comment) -> IoResult<()> {

 2226              comments::Mixed => {

 2228                  try!(zerobreak(&mut self.s));

 2230                  zerobreak(&mut self.s)
 2231              }

 2236                      // whitespace

 2238                          try!(word(&mut self.s, *line));
 2239                      }
 2240                      try!(hardbreak(&mut self.s));
 2241                  }
 2242                  Ok(())
 2243              }
 2244              comments::Trailing => {

 2249                  } else {
 2250                      try!(self.ibox(0u));
 2251                      for line in cmnt.lines.iter() {
 2252                          if !line.is_empty() {
 2253                              try!(word(&mut self.s, *line));
 2254                          }
 2255                          try!(hardbreak(&mut self.s));
 2256                      }
 2257                      self.end()
 2258                  }

 2260              comments::BlankLine => {
 2261                  // We need to do at least one, possibly two hardbreaks.
 2262                  let is_semi = match self.s.last_token() {
 2263                      pp::String(s, _) => ";" == s,
 2264                      _ => false
 2265                  };
